## Implementation Notes

### Architecture
- Build on `DepthEffect` base class from P3-VD35
- Integrate with `ShaderToyEngine` from VJlive-2 if available
- Implement particle system with custom GLSL shaders
- Use depth-driven particle parameters: position, velocity, color, size
- Support compute shaders for GPU-accelerated simulation
- Implement particle lifecycle: spawn, update, render, kill

### Performance Optimizations
- Use GPU compute shaders for particle simulation (CUDA/OpenGL)
- Precompute particle lookup tables
- Use shared memory for particle buffer access
- Implement particle LOD for distance

### Memory Management
- Allocate particle buffer: particle_count × 32 bytes
- Use ring buffer for particle recycling
- Profile memory with 100000 particles, enforce < 2GB peak
- Free shader resources after use

### Safety Rails
- Enforce particle_count ≤ 100000, simulation_steps ≤ 10
- Clamp depth_influence_strength to [0.0, 1.0]
- Validate shader_code compilation
- Fallback to CPU simulation if compute shader unavailable

